					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13290860#post-4634215</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13290860/dead-weight-don-t-kill-the-vibe#post-4634215</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2020 20:50:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Robin's arc doesn't come across naturally to me, I felt like while they became more familiar with the unwinding world they were in as the logs progressed I didn't really get a strong sense of their development and the ending fell flat for me. A lot of effort here in exploring a difficult-to-explain concept in a communicable way. The imagery is, as others have said, bold, and definitely show a unique style that encourages me to read other articles connected to this (which I assume there are, given the other comments here). There's more that works here than doesn't though, I think if you cut the poem which to me feels forced and punched up the end a little more this would be an excellent article. I still think it's pretty much good. +1</p> <p>e: I really hate the title though. I hate it a lot. It doesn't fit the article tonally and made me think this was going to be a lot less intelligent than it ended up being.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
