					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13290860#post-4629843</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13290860/dead-weight-don-t-kill-the-vibe#post-4629843</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2020 01:22:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Christopoulos</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4969651</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;My&nbsp;thoughts.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;My&nbsp;thoughts.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>So, uh&#8230; What's the deal with this still being 4736 - [ACCESS DENIED] on the mainlist, but having a numberless page title here? I get if it's a format screw, but it feels like something went wrong in the upload process more than that.</p> <p>Additionally, if &quot;DEAD WEIGHT ≡ DON'T KILL THE VIBE&quot; is the intended title of the skip, it <em>really</em> does not fit. The &quot;DON'T KILL THE VIBE&quot; part feels especially out-of-place given the high-scope stuff the article's dealing with.</p> <p>This article is pretty fantastic, though the first of the logs is by far the strongest. The rest lose themselves a little too much in imagery without making much of importance happen till the end. The kafkaesque stuff only really exists in the beginning and end of the addendum. If everything kept the same level of quality and consistency as that first log, I could see this landing in my <em>favorites.</em> Unfortunately, it doesn't.</p> <blockquote> <p>Subject is traveling through a valley which breaths with the wind,</p> </blockquote> <p><em>Breathes</em> is the verb form. <em>Breaths</em> is a plural noun.</p> <p>All that being said, this skip still gets an upvote from me pretty easily.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>+1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
